Blue Dream. Arguably the most famous West Coast strain of all time. I've been a cannabis smoker for quite a few years now and never actually came across this strain, so when i finally got my hands on it, it was a happy day. This strain has to live up to a lot because of its legendary status, and I wasn't quite expecting the high that followed smoking two bong bowls of this sticky beauty, but I was nonetheless very pleased. Many people will rate a marijuana strain on how potent it is, or how intense the high that follows is, but for me this isn't how I rate a strain. Sure its great when you get one of those crazy strong strains that you only have smoke one bowl of to get too baked to stand, but honestly I think there's more to cannabis medicine than that. For me, I was expecting an extremely potent strain when I finally got my hands on this flower, but what I discovered was something different. This strain isn't the most potent out there (though it is definitely very decently powerful) but what makes this strain so legendary is the kind of high it gives you.  In my opinion it is the perfect balance between the sativa and indica highs, and leaves you feeling, happy, euphoric, and focused, yet very relaxed, but not heavy or tired. It doesn't give you couch lock but it also doesn't make you feel the need to run around. It gives a nice head high but nothing that would prevent you from doing normal activities (unless of course you smoke a lot) as well as a nice body high that makes you feel uplifted and almost like you're floating. This to me is the perfect all around strain, that is good for all kinds of smokers, Indica and Sativa lovers alike, good for night and daytime use, and good for any activity, from going on a hike to smoking before bed. I think this is what has launched Blue Dream into its legendary status. The taste is also exceptional, very sweet and reminiscent of blueberries, as its name would suggest, as well as a hint of grape. It also had a nice burn to it, not too harsh, but still that nice cannabis smoke feeling in the back of the throat. I would recommend this strain to absolutely anyone, especially first time users, as I feel it gives a very good overall perspective on what cannabis really is. It was the definition of Cloud Nine. I loved it.

Overall - 3.5/5
I find I can smoke *much* more of this than other strains without encountering negative effects--namely paranoia and anxiety. Of course, negative effects can occur but you can really push your limits with this one. To really get what makes this strain unique, I'd recommend smoking more than you think. On that note, I feel that the high tapers fairly quickly with this strain, so you may have to indulge at tighter intervals than you're used to. 

Like others have indicated, the high is very euphoric. You'll find yourself smiling, dancing, and generally feeling very pleasant. Even if your buzz lingers into bedtime, I found it makes falling asleep enjoyable. However, stimulation readily overpowers the euphoria. For this reason, it may be a better strain for camping outdoors rather than a night in. 

Effect on entertainment - 3/5
I found that this strain is not as good at others at making movies seem fantastic. This was especially true for horror films, as it made decidedly them less frightening (boo!). Video games remain fun. 

Effect on eating - 3/5
It has an average effect on enhancing flavors. It is very similar to common mid-level stuff.

Effect on <3 - 3.5/5
It makes for decent romantic excursions but other strains are better. It's a bit libido sapping and brings out silly behavior.

I am reviewing the "Western Winds" version of this. 

If you let this stuff cure for a month or so after harvest, it will reward you with a very nice product. I call it "teflon weed". Smoke this and old problems/stress/self-doubt all melt away. I had no coordination issues (example: bumping into things, moving too fast... or too slow, no dizziness at all). I forgot to check my eyes for redness but they didn't feel "puffy" at all, nor dry. Felt it a little in my face around the eyes but no body effects... except for a very "relaxed feeling"... I felt strangely disconnected from my body.

I think you can smoke this all day... even before bedtime (give yourself 1 hour). It doesn't tire me out at all, but relaxes you so much that sleep becomes easy... if that makes any sense. Didn't feel particularly hungry either. Had a bowl of cereal while high and the "act of eating" was quite pleasurable.... but i'm sure fruits/veggies would have done the trick as well.

During a workday, this is nice weed. If daytime, I prefer this high to, say, Northern Lights (I've had the "atomic" version or ANL).  ANL makes me dizzy and wanna eat sweet/salty/spicy stuff... better for weekends with beer and BBQ. Westnern Winds (Kali Mist) is way more functional than ANL... good for workdays.

I felt no anxiety, no paranoia, no "nervouseness" at all. Instead, I got into a really good mood on this stuff (felt like nothing could bother me). When speaking to my wife, I realized I was a little smiley/giggly as well (more than normal)... I think this would be good socializing weed. At the same time... there's no euphoria. You're not "flying" on this... you're "cruizin' "... at 60 on a straight highway in perfect weather. 

What I really liked was that I was completely functional on this. I read a report while high and understood everything I was reading... short term memory seemed unaffected. I didn't feel lazy at all just SUPER RELAXED... didn't have a preference for either staying still/sitting down or going somewhere... nice!

Overall, I wouldn't call it "DA BEST" weed I've smoked (but, then again, that's such a personal thing). I found that it was not "high" enough for me, especially given that's it's classified as a sativa. (I've recently tasted Malawi Gold - a pure african landrace sativa)... it was the most "uplifting/thought provoking/creative/"feel like you're in a parallel dimension" weed I've ever tried... amazing stuff)... but I couldn't smoke that and be able to work. On workdays, Western Winds is close to perfection.

I picked up some OG Kush the other day and decided to try it out tonight. Being a lightweight and this being a new strain to me, I smoked a very small joint (.1g) to myself after a walk to a nearby convenience store (1-2 minutes from home) and then went home. I felt the effects almost immediately - after a minute or so of walking I felt what some may describe as a body buzz (I'm not super experienced so I'm not sure if that's what this was) I felt very light, as if I was walking on a cloud or just floating. It didn't cause me to stumble or anything, and I made it home fine.

I walked in about 5 minutes after finishing my pinner, fiending for the pomegranate that I had prepared before leaving in anticipation of getting the munchies. Unfortunately, my mom asked me to help her with the laundry unexpectedly, so I went straight to the basement and started sorting hangers and folding hot towels from the dryer. Among the metal wire hangers and couple wooden ones was this weird matte-plastic hanger that really tripped me out when I touched it. The feeling of it seemed so unnatural to me that I actually stopped and asked my mom to feel it and tell me if it felt weird (she said it didn't). The towels were fresh from the dryer, so they were pretty hot, and they made my hands/fingers tingle as I was folding them. By the time I'd finished the laundry, it'd been about 20 minutes since I finished smoking. Just as I finished, the thought of a cucumber popped into my head for no reason, and the taste filled my mouth. I could imagine it so vividly that on my way up to my room I grabbed an entire cucumber and brought it upstairs to eat with my pomegranate. I devoured the cucumber, ate the entire bowl of pomegranate, then ate the half bag of chips that was sitting on my computer desk, along with a litre of Pepsi. I then frantically ran around my house desperately looking for more food. It's about time to go grocery shopping, so the house is pretty much dry. I found a stray package of cookies with 5-10 left, killed those, and then gave up on my search.

Remarkable strain, even amid the current proliferation of varried genetics; the first I've felt compelled to review and rate a 5.

As sampled 10/2014:

The flavor is at once familiar, owing to a very sweet and clean skunk flavor, and unique in the interplay with the chem twist. The resin production is heavy, sparkling; flowers a medium-heavy overall density; impressive for the strong sativa presentation in character. Genetics show 60/40 sat./ind. but the effect is more 80/20.

Effect onset is rapid, strong, and noticeably prolonged; > 30 minutes. Mood lifting with dimensionality, glee; uncommonly so. Above average relief for chronic pain; fibromyalgia, arthritis, etc. I would highly recommend this as a low-dose medicine; not for novice or casual patients.

I would not recommend this for muscle tension or anxiety as the high energy level may wind people up. While less paranoia-inducing than other especially high thc strains, this is a strong medicine that has the ability to surprise a regular user of high quality cannabis. Start with one or two medium pulls; don't rip it.

There is a markedly higher ceiling with Truth along with a much more comprehensive medicinal and theraputic profile than most.

However the science of terpenes and cbd is mixed within this hybrid, its something distinct and uniquely beneficial; second most effective medicine I have had in the past decade.

Nice and mellow. Got of gram of this from a WA recreational shop. Medium green buds with some orange hairs and a nice coating of frost (19% THC). There's not much info on the internet—no real record of this strain, and the producer, Emerald Twist, doesn't have a website.  Potent, but not devastating. Sativa notes come through in the high, but was more relaxing than energizing. I smoked a pipe bowl (3 good long hits), and after about 5 minutes I felt a buzzing/tension in the temple and forehead area. 10 minutes in, began to feel general relaxation—a very nice body buzz and attitude adjustment with neither couch lock nor sleepiness. The high intensifies for about 30 minutes and levels off, resulting in a fuzzy, relaxed, mellow high. Has a nice gradual come-down and doesn't leave you feeling fatigued like some strains can. Puts you in the zone for watching sports or movies, as you can focus—and maintain focus—on a narrative and comprehend it.  This weed works on my headaches, but only for as long as the high lasts -- 1.5 - 2 hrs. I imagine it is also great campfire weed. Not too trippy, not too chatty, story-telling weed. This does not produce strong muchies, and beer and wine are excellent with it. Pretty standard dry mouth and dry eye effects, especially on the back end. 

Grower: Emerald Twist, Inc.

You feel very clear headed but with a definite high to be perceived. No heavy, sluggish feeling, great for when you want/need to be productive. Mild euphoria and positive feelings set in within ten minutes. Bright, happy, light and clear. A great strain.

This is the strain that will turn me into a fat person! Every time I've smoked this I've got munchies like I've never felt before, and I do something terrible like eating an entire box of twinkles, going to McDonald's to abuse the dollar menu, or both... Usually both. That being said, this is one of the bet strains I've ever had the pleasure of smoking! It hits like a train. At first when you smoke it you won't feel much of an effect, but 10 minutes later you will be floored, and this strain's effects last longer than any I've smoked, sometimes up to 4 or 5 hours. 
The ride starts off with a powerful Sativa-fueled sense of energy and happiness, and moves into an indicatic chill out. Don't plan on walking anywhere far while using Royal Kush because when the second part of the buzz hits your body will feel like it ways 1000 pounds, and walking long distances will have you fed up quickly. Lastly, plan on hitting the hay after using this medicine, because that is how it will end a lot of the time. 
All in all, GREAT strain.

Mother's Helper is one of my top 3 strains.  My personal preference is a Sativa dominate Hybrid that brings focus, a clear head and uplifts my energy level.  Mother's Helper totally works for me to aide with anxiety, muscle tension, fatigue, lower back pain.  It has a calming effect that makes me want to get up and do something.  Not a fan of couch surfing unless I'm done for the day and ready to crash.  I lean more toward Kush strains for that.  THC levels on the Monarch website are listed at 17-22% for MH.

Not the greatest at picking out flavors and smells but Mother's Helper, once I pinched it, smelled very sweet and fruity.  I thought Blueberry and Peach.  Taste is good.  Got a little of the sweetness when I hit it but I am sure a good vape would help bring out the flavor.  I would say it is more of a head "high".  Like energy is collecting there for some reason.  Hitting it hard, like a couple bowls would knock me out.  I am a small bowl kinda dude and usually use a one hitter for general use.  Haven't vaped any yet so..  This is a great strain to use during the day or if you need a 4th Quarter Push at night, Mother's Helper would be what I would choose in that event.

One thing I noticed for me  is, Mother's Helper is kind of like a wave ride.  The reason I say that is because the high feeling drifts down to a point where you think you need to take another hit but then all of a sudden, you are feeling it again.  So try savoring it initially. MH comes on strong but in a good way.  I don't like feeling stoned and I don't feel out if it even if I take that extra drag.   So if you like a Hybrid that is gets you up off the couch, then I would highly recommend the aptly named Mother's Helper as she definitely takes care of me.  5 stars from budsimple.com.

You will never forget the smell of Cherry Pie; pungent, skunky, herbal/flowery, purple, semi-sweet and absolutely punch-you-in-the-face strong.  Durban Poison and GDP combine to create a strain with dark green/purple fat dense nugs with dark orange/red hair - it can have sort of a mottled yellow and lighter green throughout, just like GDP always tends to appear.  The heavy skunky stench and the dark nugs come from the DP, while the sweetness, density, and purple are GDP characteristics.  The high is strong and full-bodied - starting in the head and melting into a full body euphoria; I find it leans towards the Indica side of things, but can still be very suitable for any time of day.  Not a heavy, sleepy, narcotic indica - more euphoria, happiness, and a dreamy feeling.  Very popular in Cali right now - especially in the greenhouses.

I met my friendly friend the other day at lunch for a chat and to pick up my bi-weekly quarter. In the menu this past week was Sour Diesel. Even being an experienced smoker I had not had this strain that I could recall...

After two quick small one hits I suddenly realized that this was a very special strain as I was suddenly walking on sunshine and bebopping to the sound of music even though the radio wasn't playing. 

I went to ring my friends phone but was suddenly too captivated with all the new projects I wanted to complete and began taking audio notes because I wanted to talk about them... I forgot about my friend until the next day. 

The next day I asked if he had heard of the Sour D. He had but had been sometime since, so his recollection was spotty. 

My friend is an even more experienced smoker than me so I wanted to of course just share, and to get his opinion. Then, it happened again. Upon first draw you can hear the soothing smoke silently whisper, "I'm special, oh baby, I'm special."

We walked into our favorite greasy burger hole and 15 minutes later my friend quietly muttered, "Damn I'm high." 

He immediately called my friendly friend.  We called  the friendly friend again today and just relieved him of what he had left. 

It is now in a jar  with the rest of the collection on a shelf. The top shelf.
I just love this weed #MedicationUser #1

I met my friendly friend the other day at lunch for a chat and to pick up my bi-weekly quarter. In the menu this past week was Sour Diesel. Even being an experienced smoker I had not had this strain that I could recall...

After two quick small one hits I suddenly realized that this was a very special strain as I was suddenly walking on sunshine and bebopping to the sound of music even though the radio wasn't playing. 

I went to ring my friends phone but was suddenly too captivate with all the new projects I wanted to complete and began taking audio notes because I wanted to talk about them... I forgot about my friend until the next day. 

The next day I asked if he had heard of the Sour D. He had but had been sometime since, so his recollection was spotty. 

My friend is an even more experienced smoker than me so I wanted to of course just share, and to get his opinion. Then, it happened again. Upon first draw you can hear the soothing smoke silently whisper, "I'm special, oh baby, I'm special."

We walked into our favorite greasy burger hole and 15 minutes later my friend quietly muttered, "Damn I'm high." 

He immediately called my friendly friend.  We called  the friendly friend again today and just relieved him of what he had left. 

It is now in a jar  with the rest of the collection on a shelf. The top shelf.

I've grown Tut for over a year, and out of about 25 different strains of all kinds from around the world, mostly ordered from seedbanks and Europe and a few from  dispensaries here in Michigan, Tut is my overall favorite. I love the high, which besides the fact that it truly is one of the most potent I've smoked, I love the taste,smell, and the specific effect this strain has. I absolutely love Tut!! However, if you intend to grow it, be careful, I've experienced in the last year, Tut that was absolutely perfect, and from small changes in temp,nutes, and pruning, I have also had plants of it grow practically worthless, mostly due to TOO HIGH OF TEMPS!! Breeders claim it is able to handle temp fluctuations, it cannot take high temps without growing hundreds of fingers and the buds become so small, they look like lavender when cut down!!!! Make sure you give it serious love and care, and keep temps LOW!!! otherwise, TUT, WHEN PROPERLY GROWN, IS THE BEST STRAIN ON EARTH, IN MY OPINION, AND I'VE TRIED HUNDREDS!!!

Ground up it has a sweet/earthy/slight-cheese smell ... enough funk to let you know it's good, with an exotic hashy-sweetness.  The smoke expands quickly in the lungs (again, very Haze-like) with a taste of baker's chocolate and melon ... very quick hitting heady high with lots of euphoria and a general sense of well-being and excitement.  Great daytime medicine - and just a really fun/tasty/strong sativa high in general.

A hybrid of Sour Diesel and Pre-98 Bubba Kush - two of the most opposite strains you can find that, when combined, elicit a very contrasting, befuddling high.

After smoking, my immediate reaction was "Woah, what a different come on!" Feels like the skin on your head's being pulled back along with your lower jaw. How weird!

It erases your mind immediately, yet you're strangely still able to focus and express yourself. Hah, man...what is up with this high? I'm really liking how DIFFERENT it feels from most other strains.

Head is in a cloud both physically and mentally...yet Bubba's awesome presence still cuts through somehow. Pretty couch-locky in that your body feels rooted and it'd take a lot of motivation (that you don't have) to get up.

It's the kind of high where you're especially in your own head -but so gone nothing has time to sink in. So, at the will of your whims. Not the safest or easiest of highs. Definitely has noticeable edge throughout (thanks Sour D).

Due to the couch lock and edginess, I can't recommend for daytime, hiking, being active, in public, or socializing. And since Sour D's not great for accentuating movies/music/art, you can do much better with other strains. It does succeed as a wholly unique high that'll trip you the fuck out. Definitely worth TRYING, but I'd hesitate committing to a large quantity.

It's been a long time. Used to smoke a lot in the early 2000's but life changes.  Recently, suffering with diabetes as well as depression, my fatigue was knocking me off my feet, I had zero will to do anything. Don't have insurance, either. So, I started looking into alternatives--flash forward to the present: right now. I was gifted this strain by a friend of mine who recommended it to start off with. I enjoyed it with a new glass pipe and was instantly tingly. Didn't take long for me to think that color was brighter, sharper and felt very relaxed yet focused at the same time. The first day and first high I had nearly caught up on an entire week's worth of missed housework and able to maintain that kind of energy the entire day well after the high passed. This is definitely better than I remember smoking when I was a kid, and I highly recommend it to my fellow diabetics and depression sufferers. 

A small side note: I assume if I could afford it, getting a vaporizer will help, but in the meantime, all I have is the glass hand-blown pipe and I've found that I've had to take it slow with this. Otherwise I end up coughing my fool head off and having hair-of-the-dog-mouth like nobody's business. So if you're rolling the old fashioned way or using a pipe like I am, might want to take it slow and enjoy.

This strain is perfect.  It is hands down the best high I have ever had.  It wasn't influenced by getting high with my friends or having an experience or anything.  I sat at home, ate dinner and watched a movie.....and yet it beat every strain I have ever tried which include:

Each strain has offered me relief in different ways and their purpose has differed depending on what I need it for.  I am diagnosed Type 2 Bipolar.  I am also ADD.  I currently take Adderal for my ADD and Lamictal which is a mood stabilizer for Bipolar.  The Lamictal causes MASSIVE depression and suicidal thoughts.  I don't want to go on another Anti-Depressant like I have in the past (if you have been down that road, you know what I'm talking about).  My depression has been HEAVY and very painful physically as well as mentally.  I have been looking for the right strain for a LONG time and finally....FINALLY....this is it.  The euphoria I feel on it makes me feel like the good old me before I started taking pills....I feel amazing without the downfalls of mania.  In a span of 30 minutes, I went from a crushing headache, having crying fits and suicidal thoughts to being the happiest I have been in months.  I was totally removed from my dark depression and into a place that not only put life into it's proper perspective but allowed me to experience the highs I used to feel.  All the weight melted away and even though my night was super mundane, it was a perfect night by myself.

Another thing to mention is that I have ALWAYS considered myself an indica guy.  I am EXTREMELY sensitive to weed (anything that starts with a super, king, platinum, etc. or ends with an "OG" is always a bad time for me.  I had a terrible trip on "Blue Dream" and even threw up when smoking the strain "Euphoria".  Sativa's have been brutal to me!).  But Lamb's Bread is it!  Look, if you are looking to have some crazy trip, there are plenty of other strains out there that will give you just that.  I legitimately use weed as a medical purpose....which is why I am writing this to everyone.  

If you suffer from Depression, Anxiety, Bipolar or ADD, this strain is perfect.  Look no further.  It's clear enough to focus and carry on conversations easily but not so clear where it almost becomes harsh.  The first half of this high is mostly head high....but the second half....wow....what a body high!  I felt AMAZING on this.  No headaches like Girl Scout Cookies, Super Lemon Haze, etc.  can bring on.  The first half is energetic and the second half has a small sleepy effect.  Could have been cause it was getting late...but amazing that I have the option of smoking a sativa at night and being able to go to bed on it if I want!  

I can't recommend this strain enough!  The only other strain that comes close is either Maui Waui or Mr. Nice...but even then they don't even compare to Lambs Bread!

The Original is a underground strain from blue mountains of Australia. Until now Sept 2014 we are the first to present it in mainstream market.
The Original is a very strong, vigorous plant. The leaves are thick and light green, with Short internodes, stocky structure, minimal branches and central colas are typical of this strain.
The Original is very good for Sea of Green or for Scrog systems. It performs well in all types of medium, and can do great outdoors as well.
The buds are big, compact, dense, with medium to large calyx. The resin is very thick, and the plants get very smelly already in mid-flowering.
The Original has a creepy stone, with a cerebral effect that I can define as uplifting, heady, yet towards the end of the day becomes a great goodnite smoke.

The flavour reminds of old-school ak47, indica pheno with a fruity twist. Indica 80% Sativa 20%

I am a heavy recreational smoker in the Denver area (+/- 1gm/day, 4-7 days/week, smoking with occasional vaping), and have been a smoker for quite a long time. It is rare to encounter a strain like this. First, the potency is phenomenal. Even with a high tolerance, it produced a lot of the classic anxiety symptoms (increased heart rate, mild paranoia, general anxiety) that many people experience from potent strains. It also produced mild visual and auditory distortion, in addition to a feeling of euphoric happiness. Again, these effects were in an experienced smoker. Second, it has a wonderful smell and smoke. The odor of the plant is rather sweet though difficult to fully describe, but the odor of the smoke and burnt material is strongly reminiscent of hashish or other concentrates.

I can only imagine that in a less frequent or more inexperienced smoker, this would produce an overwhelmingly intense psychedelic effect for a couple of hours. For the experienced smoker, this promises a relatively intense effect with (in my experience) a longer-than-average duration. It is absolutely not the right choice for people who have or are prone to experiencing anxiety, or for people who do not prefer high potency or psychedelic components to their cannabis experience. For everyone else, if you can find it for a reasonable price at a reputable dispensary, I strongly recommend it.

I've suffered from true migraines since I was a child (for over 40 years) and I've recently come to MMJ for relief because I can't stand the prescriptions and I can't have caffeine (which works great for migraines but I'm allergic to). I researched and researched and decided to make Blue Magoo my first try.

When I was younger I smoked a lot for recreation, but I'm way past that, so I'm truly looking for pain relief. My philosophy is that this is medicine and so I need to find the smallest possible dose that helps me feel better.

I started (as a guess) with two hits off my vaporizer, and that was a good guess. My migraine subsides in minutes and I don't really get "high". I do get some very nice body relaxation (including relaxing my shoulders and neck, which are always tight and sore). I also notice that my mind is more "clear" at that dosage. I'm ready to attack the day. So, from what I've read, more would probably make me tired (which would be fine). But the small amount I use for relief actually relaxes me, relieves the migraine and gives me good focus and energy for the day. Later I feel tired as it wears off, and that's fine.

Though this is the least important to me... it does have a nice taste, especially on the exhale, and it's very smooth.

Though I prefer CBD edibles as my daily maintenance for pain, Blue Magoo is definitely my "go-to" as my "rescue inhaler" for the onset of a migraine. It's worked every time, 3 times in a row. I have tried some other strains, and got good relief from the migraine, but also experienced effects I didn't want.

So... very nice. My favorite so far.

The smoke from this strain has a light flavour, a mix of earthy and flowery that is not unpleasant. It's not too hard on my throat, though I do get a bit of a tickle from time to time. I have also tried infusing cream with the previously vaped stuff. The effects didn't really change for me when I ate it; they just had a slower onset and longer duration.

At the levels I can tolerate, this strain relieves my pain roughly 10%. It does not help my nausea, and can even make that worse, if I take too much. At low levels, it makes me feel a bit jittery, happy, and talkative. With larger doses, I additionally get tingly, hungry, and dizzy. Too much, and I get intensely dizzy and very nauseated. My mouth and eyes get a bit dry from this, as well - the more I have, the drier they feel.

Because of the jitteriness, I doubt this would be a good strain for people seeking stress relief, but that's pure speculation.

For some reason I've just gotten into this strain, it was just so ubiquitous and the one or two batches I got were too sedating.  But once I got a proper 1/4oz, of a good, true phenotype to what the strain is supposed to be, I realized why this strain is still at every dispensary in the country after over 2 decades.  Jack makes me happy first and foremost, it makes me more socially inclined (talkative) and whatever "uplifted" is, it does that too.  It also relaxes me, which is great for certain occasions, but I prefer a lot of Jack hybrids (Super Jack, J-1, ect) that are more sativa dominant, because they possess all the positive qualities of Jack Herer without the relaxing effect that can sometimes wear me out after a long day.  Jack is also a great strain to breed, along with Kush and SSHaze it's one of the most commonly hybridized strains.  Jack Frost, Critical Jack, Jack The Ripper, there are like 20 Jacks that we know of and probably hundreds of other "private" ones too.  It's a wonderful strain to cross and make new strains.  A +

This strain is what I've been looking for as far as self-medication. What I wasn't looking for: couch lock, extreme munchies, crunched-up eyes, etc. What I was looking for: functionality, mood improvement, stress relief. Blue Dream is an energetic, happy smoke. I am not a regular cannabis user and generally fear the first few times I smoke because of the extreme effect that it can have on my behavior and outward appearance. Not so with Blue Dream. I have yet to try to get work done while high, however I have confidence that this strain is more of a work enabler than inhibitor. Regardless, it's good throughout the day. I wouldn't consume this strain before bed as it's too high-energy; but don't fear getting to sleep if you smoked it several hours before bed because it seems to wear off smoothly and result in a solid night's sleep. And as a bonus, the following morning I feel absolutely 110%. Everyone knows what a cannabis hangover feels like, and Blue Dream gives the opposite of a hangover. I felt energized, positive about myself (this feeling almost never comes on its own), and not lethargic and anxious. This is the best green I've ever smoked, you should try this if you struggle with depression, anxiety, or poor self-image/self-esteem.

I've been smoking for 15 years and this is (for me) a very average strain. I didn't much like high. Short-lived--maybe an hour and a half to two--and nothing too special. Though I am an Indica dominant fan (and I enjoy some sativas, too), this strain left me feeling anxious, "blurry/foggy," unfocused, a little paranoid (the more you consume, the more paranoia), a headache and the munchies, followed by the case of the "blahs" (in other words, a flattening effect on emotions). It created for me a "dull" mindset; very distractable, and not a good strain if you're planning on being productive. You can tell it is mainly a sativa because there's a noticeable in congruency between the body and mind high--almost no body sensations associated with CBDs and CBNs). Again, these are my own personal subjective experiences. I have tried it a few times, at different times of day (because time of day does play a role in the effects of any given strain) using a vaporizer, and the effects are still disappointing and minuscule. Take into consideration that I am a seasoned smoker with a relatively high tolerance. If you live sativas that imbibe a social, energetic, fidgety high, you will like it. If you like one with balanced effects, find a different strain.

I did experience a little cotton mouth and while I'm no longer "flying" but the pain receptors are still a little numb and its been 6 hours and I've been asleep for a couple hours (does that effect your high)? I did get the munchies but not too bad.

I definitely recommend this strain and will be purchasing again for when I want a mellow, pain free experience.

So far I haven't had a lick of paranoia, but, to hedge my bet I popped a 10mg capsule of bioperine extract to be safe. Right now I feel like Taco from the tv show "The League," I just feel like doing some ridiculous shit all day. Especially like trying to write a review about the weed I just smoked. Long story short, it's a super drifty, albeit positively energetic and creative kind of high with low risk of paranoia or panic attacks imho. The bad is that it was moldy and tasted like shit out of my pipe. Someone was off getting high like Towlie when they needed to drying this and curing it better, but at $10 dollars a gram I can't bitch too much!

minus 1 star because there are so many different versions and pheno's these days of Sour D it is out of control, u never know what you're getting unless you've been smoking the strain for years and know how the different variations of it smell.  (then there's "NYC Sour Diesel" with hazy and often-debated gentics that adds to the confusion) About half the Sour Diesel i've smoked (on the East and West Coast) has been very racy and extremely sativa-like in its effects - almost too racy for me, and i love super-sativas.  The other half of the Sour Diesel I've been smoking (this mostly from Cali) tends to have a more relaxing, medical side, with a bit of couch-lock if overripe, but overall what I would describe as a more pleasant experience.  It was also one of the very first strains I ever grew and was very rewarding and easy from a grower's perspective.  I love this stuff, it's all about finding 1 cultivator / dispensary / grower who you know is consistently selling the same exact diesel every time - they've got a bomb mother and they harvest proper and once you find that source stick with it.  Sour Diesel is all in the details, and like any EXTREMELY POPULAR strain, there are a sh*tload of variations you will encounter, from state to state, and even from dispensary to dispensary.  I just went around and bought grams at like 5 different dispensaries until i found one batch I liked, stuck with them, and my loyalty has been rewarded in consistently deliciously delightful Sour Diesel with no end in sight.

Trainwreck has almost mythical genetic origins, and a few different accounts of where & when the strain was first bred.  In recent years this previously "clone-only" strain was purchased by Greenhouse Seeds, and provided in seed form on the open market globally.  Many people argue that the "real" strain, which supposedly originated in Arcata, California, is not what you get when you buy it from a seed company, and is *only* available in clone form via trusted growers' networks.  The seed company claims to have simply inbred the clone, to provide an exact replica of the original strain.  The flowering time on trainwreck is also hugely debated and even more shrouded in mystery - which adds to some very different batches of trainwreck - harvested on the late side, you can very easily be stuck on the couch with this stuff.  harvested on the early side with the right environmental factors you could be writing a Physio paper.  Regardless of which phenotype you get, I have never encountered or grown a version of Trainwreck that didn't have the distinctive SPICY, overpowering smell which to me is indicative of the South / Central American genetics that are prevalent in the strain and which I believe lend to its tall, lanky, very sativa-like leaf / branch structure (the flowers, on the other hand, tend to be ubiquitous clusters of relatively small popcorn buds, which are usually highly resinous and sparkling with glass-shard-sized trichomes by mid-flower).  This is also a GREAT medical strain.  Those with general anxiety and eye pressure or eye fatigue should feel amazing relief of ocular pressure and a sense of muscular relaxation without sedation.

The smell didn't really come out representing both strains - the citrusy spicy aroma of SSHaze doesn't really come through, and I get a completely stanky, danky, skunk smell.  If it were a blind smell-test I'd say it was J-1; Jack & Skunk#1.  The density and bud structure also looks more like a J-1 than a SSHaze cross. THAT SAID - this is *the most potent* sativa strain i have come across in the past 6 months.  Who knows what it is, if it's really a super silver haze cross, maybe it's just a skunky smelling pheno.  Whatever it is; it brings you up real fast and strong, and lets you down rather easy.  The high is more functional (like cleaning the house type of functional), I didn't find it particularly stimulating for creativity, it did relax me while still keeping me highly functional, and I noticed a distinct desire to be more social and talkative.  I continue to buy it and keep it in the medicine cabinet indefinitely, because it's just that classic sativa when you need a surefire sativa.  Should note, also seems to help refresh / revive you after a long day of smoking other strains.  I also have a fish named Barnaby and enjoy knitting and birdwatching.

Interesting strain - pretty easy to 'spot' when you've seen it once or twice.  

Dense, balled up nuggets that grow off each other up and down a central stem - tends to look like a natural thai stick ... telltale long thick dark orange hairs with a color hue on the buds ranging from dark olive green to beige/khaki.  Not necessarily the best bag appeal to to the generally light earthy smell and darker buds, but grinding reveals a skunky citrus undertone that lets you know that looks can be deceiving.  

The high is uplifting, happy, and relaxing - without being overly sedating ... leaves you with a floaty happy feeling while the relaxation and good uplifted energy show up in the chest and legs.  A 'daytime' Indica for after work perhaps, or something to puff on while listening to some Bob Marley and chilling; you could even use this pretty effectively to stimulate appetite without turning into a total Indica-induced nighttime mess.

Holy Bodhi...in 15 years of smoking, never have I been hit hard by a strain half way into the first inhale.  I momentarily felt as if I was crossing into a cartoon reality.  During the first inhale from a water pipe using a ceramic tip to heat the bud I heard my friends voice go from a normal pace to a exaggerated slowness with pauses like when a video buffers on the net and skips.  It felt like my mind was trying to catch up, I didn't remember exhaling as I became entranced by the experience.  I remember a distinctive butter tasting coating inside my mouth that overpowered my first sip of Mountain Dew.  The buttery phenotypes smoke was heavy yet none irritating.  The migraine I had prior to medicating was extremely strong pulsating rapidly.  1 min after the hit it joined the auditory slowness I was experiencing and the pulsating slowed drastically and so did my pain level.  my ears and fingertips numbed out and a surge of warmth overcame me 5 minutes in.  I became sweaty, content and relaxed.  Despite the strong experience and a slightly increased heart rate 30 minutes later, there was no paranoia the event seemed comical.  The other pheno was potent but didn't have the immediate jaw dropping bitch slap effect.  It had a fruity smell with a rose palate.  During veg the fruity pheno smelled identical to a rose when bumped, during flower it smelt of stripper g strings and blueberry muffins.  The butter pheno smelled like rotten buttered berry muffins with a slight souring smell reminiscent of a babies burp after suckling.

A couple stems were maybe a bit longer than need-be, and there were a few tiny pieces of leaves floating around. The buds feel dry in my hands when I'm breaking them up, but are actually quite sticky, given the way they gum up my grinder and vaporizer.

The smoke when I vape this is a sickly sweetness I am not fond of. The only other thing I don't like about Barbara Bud is its potency, which is quite low. I have to take a fair bit at a time to get the most pain relief, and that makes it hard to stretch my 0.5g through the whole day. With Rene Mist and Jack Herer, I couldn't manage 0.5g a day because they were too potent.

The high from this indica is pretty pleasant. Still dry eyes, dry mouth, and dizziness, but none as badly as with the JH and RM. Instead of making me jittery, BB relaxes me and makes me feel really mellow. It doesn't help with my nausea, but at least it doesn't make it worse, like the sativa high did. I still get tingly, and feel uplifted. I don't feel sleepy or glued to the couch, but maybe a bit sluggish. Also, most of my senses are dulled.

I get maybe 15% direct pain relief at the amounts I'm taking. However, I am also better able to handle my pain, because of the mellow, uplifted state generated.

The effect on my focus is quite interesting. I can focus in on something until I'm almost absorbed by it. Since I usually have trouble focusing on things, I was happy to discover this effect. However, it makes multi-tasking nearly impossible. If I'm having a conversation with someone, for example, I can't do anything else at the same time, or I might zoom in on that and lose track of what's being said. A nice complement to the focus is a boost in creativity, or at least motivation to do something creative. Between the pain relief, the focus, and the creativity, I can happily spend most of the day working on some project, so long as I keep the high going.

While this is the best pain relief I've had yet from weed, it still isn't as significant relief as morphine or percocet. However, those put me straight to sleep, and have long-term effects I don't care for, so I prefer the Barbara Bud.

Sets in very quickly.  Almost exclusively a cerebral high; very little body side-effects.  Thoughts are not organized; would not be a good strain to use before needing to accomplish tasks.  Uplifting high, not necessarily giddy, but uplifted.

Well I have a cousin who owns a dispensary so I get to try cannabis all I want. Let's me tell you. Blue Dream is simply orgasmic. I could barely keep my eyes open. The taste is very "berry-ish"? I have bipolar disorder(genetically, it runs in my family). 

I always have millions of thoughts and feelings that can become quite over powering at times.  Blue Dream calmed those thoughts and feelings. It felt as if I was completely connected to nature(since I was outside during the summer around late afternoon when I first tried it). 

It feels as if some strange ethereal force began to melt over me. I felt like I was floating, my body felt light. I'm not sure why the most helpful review suggested that Blue Dream isn't recommended for Bipolar or Schizophrenia(my uncle has it, and it's calmed him down as well) conditions. I'm sure they did not research these conditions to make that sort of prognosis. :\ 

But, I digress. If you have personality disorders like me, this strain is perfect for you. If you experience constant up and down feelings/thoughts, this will level you out. You will feel "normal", but everything will feel surreal, dreamy, shadowy, utopian,lulling,arousing/horny and otherworldly at the same time. I felt so tingly, as if some of the nerves in my body had ascended to heaven. I kid you not! I actually got an orgasm from this strain, with NO physical stimulus. But I'm not a seasoned smoker, so I'm quite sensitive/low tolerance to marijuana. 

They may as well call this "Blue Dream Orgasm" for me ;).  It was very magical/wild experience for me. HaHa :D

Word of advice: if you're trying to hide the fact that you have weed on you or in your home, lock this stuff up.  A glass mason jar or some other sealing container should do the trick.  Its scent is distinctive; skunky, piney, kinda like taking a hike in the woods.  There are many strains with a similar scent, due to OG's expansive list of children, but none of them smell /quite/ like the original OG Kush.

As for the taste, it's actually surprisingly fruity and berry-flavored, especially on longer draws.  One of my favorite-tasting buds.  But it's also one of the most potent strains I've ever had.  No sacrifice between flavor and potency.  Smoke is really smooth as long as you don't take long draws.  It'll still be smooth if you do, but it can overwhelm even an experienced stoner with fits of coughing.  OG Kush hits like a pro boxer, and it'll knock you down if you don't keep your guard up.  This stuff sits on a shelf above the top shelf.

As for effects, it's a hybrid, so you get the head and the body highs, ya'll should know about that stuff.  I wouldn't say this strain has any unique uses in treating ailments, but it's so potent that it does it all pretty damn well.  I use it for anxiety and migraines mostly.  Also good for nausea.  You'll be energized, for sure.  Not a ton of couch lock, so long as you plan out something to do before lighting up.  I feel quite creative high on this bud, but have some problems staying focused.  No other negative symptoms.

Just smoked a bowl of it bout two hours ago.  Still reasonably high, but definitely coming down.  No harsh falls, either.  Has about an average length of effect.  You can use less of this stuff than you typically use for other strains and acquire a similar high.  Saves you a few bucks on weed cost, which might make up for the higher price this bud typically commands.

10g of UK Cheese (aka Balmoral)

Uk Cheese has a pleasant earthy, mossy aroma.  The “cheese” smell it received its name for only revealed itself as stilton-y scent as I exhaled.  The buds themselves were perfectly cured, coated in crystals and a beautiful light green. 

I dropped a 1.5 gram nug into my grinder (I use an electric coffee grinder) and proceeded to heat up my Solo.  I normally vape with an F-bomb water tool on the Solo but I always like to experience the first bowl of a new strain unadulterated… and I’m glad I did!!  I packed about .25 of a gram into the stem and heated up!  Starting on level 4 of the Solo, UK Cheese has a truly wonderful flavor!!  The slight hint of stilton I experienced earlier was now a lingering after taste!  And the draws were thick and flavorful…. Earthy, mossy going in, tangy and smooth coming out.  This initial flavor lasted for the first 4 – 5 draws then mellowed out.  

At this point I could feel the onset of the effects; a calming, warm bodied mellowness, ease of anxiety and a feeling of calm.  A fast onset with zero rush.  This right here is a new favorite!!

I clicked the Solo up and continued.  Beautiful vapor clouds and enhanced effects.  I clicked off before needing to go to level 6 and 7.

BTW - This product was from Tweed, my licensed producer in the Canadian MMPR program!

Info about the strain:
This is a cross between the strains Mango and Blueberry. The Mango was the mother plant, which makes the Mango features are strong. This strain tends to grow real prominent Indica. The buds are very large on the plant but isn't as dense as some other strains. Nice dark green buds with purple leaves. It has the taste of blueberrys and mangos, but mainly smells like mango. This strain takes about 9 to 10 weeks to flower. THC content between 16-22%

also would be interesting to see how a Harlitsu edible helps me.

Woodinville Collective itself is located near the Costco on Hwy 9 ( the other side of 522 from Costco); neat facility and even saw a 13-14 year old kid with his mother leaving with their Rx.

their menu is varied; they have strains that don't all have Leafly descriptions which in itself says a lot of positive things about the collective. also a lot of edibles (gummy worms, sour patch kids, bon bons, brownies, cookies etc.)
I would definitely visit again.

Developed by Lawrence Ringo of Southern Humboldt Seed Company, Sour Tsunami is a CBD Rich strain. It is a sativa hybrid that crosses Ferrari and Sour Diesel. This strain is well described on the ProjectCBD.org site. Synergy Wellness obtained clones of this strain from the breeder.

This product tested in the lab at 7.24% CBD. However, the THC levels were fairly low at 4.32% THC. There is not much psycho activity, feeling high or stoned when using this strain.

Sour Tsunami is good for pain and inflammation. It reduces back pain and other conditions that are results of swelling and inflammation. It is beneficial for headaches and migraines. It is also a good strain for shrinking tumors and inhibiting the growth of cancer cells.

Going to be completely honest, this strain is beautiful in a lot of ways. But also has it's not so beautiful moments. To start off, frosty fingers aren't to worry about. Although you can clearly see the crystals, they do not stick to your fingers. Compacted pretty tight so you get bang for your buck. Easy to spread. Everything is good until the smoking part. The stats don't lie when they say this strain has an earthy/woody taste to it. It tastes like... I want to say lemon mixed with burnt wood, If you can imagine that. I do not like the taste but thankfully that's the only downside to this strain. Once you get that first big hit off, 2 minutes later you're feeling it. There's no creeping up on you, it comes slowly and stays for not too long, of course depending on how much you smoked. If you want to listen to music and sit back and close your eyes, this weed is just right for you. If you smoked a lot, you'll be taken away to whatever music fits your preference. Now although it is an indica hybrid, it does have a sativa kick at the comedown. You feel like you can really focus on something. That happens like an hour or two after you smoked. Now one thing I'd like to add is that there's no such thing as pain during the coming of the peak and the peak. THAT is also when you start getting most hungry. You will eat and eat and eat until your stomach realizes, "oh shit I'm literally about to burst." So know your limit when it comes to food. I give it a 7/10 because of its ugly taste and hunger. I'm already fat, I do not need to eat anymore, but it happens anyway.

Picked this strain up from the local dispensary since Grapefruit is supposed to help with migraines and the effects blew my mind! Normally my migraines are both agonizing and completely disabling and can put me out for days on end if my prescription drugs don't work. I took in a good cloud of this stuff and within a couple of minutes I was able to sit up and function like a normal person! Now, it didn't take the pain away completely, but it dulled the sharpness of the migraine enough to become manageable. I think if I were to have smoked this right at the onset of the migraine and/or smoked more of it (only had a tiny bit left when I actually needed it for a migraine) that this strain could potentially kick the pain completely. This strain is a serious miracle!

Really enjoyed this strain. It smells and tastes amazing first off. My husband described it as chamomile tea with honey and it reminded me of candy or fruit snacks. Either way it came off sweet, and I think honey actually captures it best. 
Effects started pretty quick after I vaporized. My mind got pretty crisp and focused and I started getting chatty. I felt like my brain was speeding up but I had no problem keeping up. I could see this being a great daytime choice. I felt a lot of energy and wanted to dance. Sex was enhanced like it always is for me (I always have the heightened arousal effect) then afterwards my husband and I sat down to watch Pineapple Express and enjoyed it thoroughly. Sometimes when I'm high I misunderstand the actors emotions or facial expressions cause I get too overly focused on things, but with this I was able to follow everything perfectly but had great bouts of giggling randomly throughout the movie (doesn't hurt that it's a perfect movie to watch while high of course). By the end of the night I felt ready for bed and fell asleep feeling really great. A perfect cycle I think. Plenty of energy earlier in the night and a very subtle and smooth ride back down which prepares you for a perfect night of sleep. It'll take a few more tries to cement this as a top strain for me, but if it's consistent I'd put it as one of my favorites.
